The paper proposes a new framework for semi-supervised training of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The method is demonstrated on several datasets, including image classification tasks, which suggests that it could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. The use of embeddings and associations also suggests that it could be relevant to topics such as representation learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of optimization schedules and penalization suggests that it could be relevant to topics such as optimization (cs.NE).
